race.comment: ZAPHOD (2) will be tough to beat building on his handsome win in a CL6 at Eagle Farm over 1825m. The middle distance won't be an issue and 2x winning rider Mallyon is reunited. Races forward and has been kept on the fresh side. TORABELLA (8) has been knocking on the door in good company and stuck on well at Eagle Farm last time beaten 1.8L at Stakes level. Steps up to a middle distance for the first time but she draws inside and it's hard to risk the premier stable. RAF ATTACK (10) has been switched back from Sydney by the Ciaron Maher yard. Fourth up now and he was beaten a whisker in the Listed Ipswich Cup over this trip at the back on his previous campaign. Had no luck last time and it won't surprise if he's in the finish. GALIFIANAKIS (5) is going well and has been kept up to the mark with a Doomben trial. He'll be around the mark with average luck from the outside gate.
